  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Thus, \"C3 + DIN\" adopts this approach to generate SQL code.",
    "LLMs have hallucination problems, that is, they can generate text that does not make sense (YU et al., 2024).",
    "In the Text-to-SQL task, an LLM can generate SQL code with incorrect syntax.",
    "Therefore, \"C3 + DIN\" incorporates DIN's self-correction mechanism, which seeks to correct the SQL code in a simple way by passing some hints to the model along with the database schema.",
    "This chapter presents experiments to assess how LLM-based Text-to-SQL strategies perform on a challenging scenario characterized by a database with a large complex schema, assuming that the schema vocabulary is close to the vocabulary of the user NL questions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "LLMs have hallucination problems, that is, they can generate text that does not make sense (YU et al., 2024)."
  ]
}